7722512a-2b26-48d5-9f8a-2fb9e8dfa706.0f627c67-66f6-4a5a-9f8c-f1b3a7fe3029.description=Adds a custom attribute to a specific object (object can be of type\: SERVERS, DEVICE_GROUPS, SOFTWARE_POLICIES, CUSTOMERS, OS_BUILD_PLANS). Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. attachedToType - The type of the objectto which the Custom Attribute is attached to (must be one of [SERVERS, DEVICE_GROUPS, SOFTWARE_POLICIES, CUSTOMERS, OS_BUILD_PLANS]. attachedToName - The name of the object to which the Custom Attribute is attached to (e.g. name of server or device group, short name of customer etc). attachedToID - The id of the object to which the Custom Attribute is attached to (e.g. id of server or device group etc). Use this input for unique identification. name - The name of the attribute. value - The value of the attribute. Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data 7722512a-2b26-48d5-9f8a-2fb9e8dfa706.12310658-c4b2-46d7-a6f6-bc81d23d5ede.description=Adds a custom attribute to a specific object (object can be of type\: SERVERS, DEVICE_GROUPS, SOFTWARE_POLICIES, CUSTOMERS, OS_BUILD_PLANS). Adds a value into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
